Late reply but you can actually do this with the library as is. It&#x27;s not designed for it so you&#x27;ll have to use fftw yourself and call some borderline internal stuff, but it ought to work the same.<p><pre><code>    float* samples = ... //load audio samples here
    int len = ...
    fftwf_plan p = fftwf_plan_r2r_1d(len,samples,samples,FFTW_REDFT10,FFTW_ESTIMATE);
    fftwf_execute(p);

    RDResolution* res;
    size_t count;
    RDMethod* m = resdet_methods();
    m->func(samples,len,1,1,&res,&count,12,m->threshold);</code></pre>

For example, if you wanted to have a title centered on the page you might do something like...<p>var page = new Page();<p>var label = new Label();
label.x = page.width/2;
label.y = page.height/2;
label.text = &quot;Hello, World!&quot;;
label.textColor = new Color(r: 1, g: 0, b: 0);<p>page.add(label);<p>etc.
